Sentencas: The highly phase-pure electrolyte materials with composition La1.9Ba0.1Mo1.9Mn0.1O9 (LBMMO) was prepared by the sol-gel auto-combustion method for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Chemical synthesis and properties of La1.9Ba0.1Mo1.9Mn0.1O9 as electrolyte for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: The details of gel's auto-combustion, phase evolution, sintering, thermal expansion and electrochemical performance of LBMMO were investigated by means of thermo-gravimetry (TG), X-ray diffraction (XRD), scanning electron microscopy (SEM), transmission electron spectroscopy (TEM), thermal expansion curve (TEC) and complex impedance spectra.
Titulo: Chemical synthesis and properties of La1.9Ba0.1Mo1.9Mn0.1O9 as electrolyte for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: The results showed that the highly phase-pure electrolyte LBMMO could be obtained after calcining at 600 degrees C.
Titulo: Chemical synthesis and properties of La1.9Ba0.1Mo1.9Mn0.1O9 as electrolyte for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: The sample sintered at 900 degrees C for 4 h in air exhibited a better sinterability, and the relative density of LBMMO was higher than 96%.
Titulo: Chemical synthesis and properties of La1.9Ba0.1Mo1.9Mn0.1O9 as electrolyte for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: The electrical conductivities of the sample were 6.7x10(-3) and 25.9x10(-3) S/cm at 700 and 800 degrees C in air, respectively.
Titulo: Chemical synthesis and properties of La1.9Ba0.1Mo1.9Mn0.1O9 as electrolyte for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: Results also showed that LBMMO had moderate thermal expansion (alpha=16.3x10(-6) K-1, between room temperature and 800 degrees C) and an electrical activation energy equal to 1.32 eV).
Titulo: Chemical synthesis and properties of La1.9Ba0.1Mo1.9Mn0.1O9 as electrolyte for IT-SOFCs
